name: The Explorer
description: Starlings are an invasive specie that usurps the dwellings of native birds. In this animation we see a space-aged starling flying through the air in search of new lands to "discover". His helmet is adorned with a Pontiac Chieftain hood ornament; yes, these are a thing that was made in America, just like the buffalo nickel and sport team logos. This identity crisis comes up every November as we try to replace Columbus Day with Indigenous People’s Day.
